# Git Conventions

## Commit Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>

[optional body]
```

### Types

| Type | When |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New game mechanic, system, or feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code refactor without behavior change |
| `data` | ScriptableObject, config, balance changes |
| `art` | Sprites, animations, UI assets |
| `test` | Tests |
| `ci` | GitHub Actions, build scripts |
| `docs` | Documentation, README |
| `chore` | Package dependencies, project settings |

### Scopes (optional)

`combat`, `units`, `ui`, `inventory`, `guild`, `ai`, `audio`, `scene`

### Rules

- Language: **English**
- Use imperative: "add", "fix", "remove" — not "added", "fixes"
- No period at the end
- Max 72 characters in subject line

### Examples

```
feat(combat): add poison damage over time mechanic
fix(units): fix archer not targeting nearest enemy
data(combat): rebalance warrior base stats
refactor(ai): extract targeting logic into separate class
chore: update Unity packages
```

